parameters:
\N<Omura> You know that part-time jobs are prohibited at
our school, right?
\N<Hinata Aki>(Why did it have to be Omura who found out...)

\N<Omura> Besides, your grades aren't exactly good either.
If you were to get a failing grade, it would be a violation
of school rules along with the part-time job.

\N<Omura> The worst case scenario is suspension... no, even
expulsion is possible... And it would also cause trouble for
the club.
\N<Omura> By the way, why did you need money, Aki?

\N<Hinata Aki> The shoes I use for club activities have
reached their limit, so when I went to buy new ones at the
store, I found myself a little short on money...
\N<Omura> I see... So that's what it was.

\N<Omura> The teacher knows that you're passionate about
the club activities, so if you had any problems, I wish you
would have consulted the adults around you.

\N<Omura> Alright, I understand! I'll pretend I didn't see
what happened this time.
\N<Omura> Ah... but I'm quitting my part-time job.

\N<Omura> If there were reports from other students or
teachers, the teacher wouldn't be able to turn a blind eye.

\N<Omura> ...That being said, Aki's academic and financial
issues are still unresolved, aren't they?

\NOmura: So, I have a suggestion from the teacher... Aki,
you...

\N<Omura> How about coming to the teacher's house to
study?

\N<Omura> And if you're willing to listen to a simple
request from the teacher, I'll even pay you for your part-
time job.

\N<Hinata Aki>(But... this is actually a pretty good deal,
isn't it...)

\N<Hinata Aki>(Not only did they overlook my part-time job,
but this will also solve both my study and financial
issues...)
\N<Omura> Is that true?! Hinata Aki studying?!

\N<Omura> Alright! Good deeds must be done quickly. Let's
immediately assess the areas you're weak in with a small
test!
\N<Hinata Aki>(Maybe I should have just quit after all...)

\N<Hinata Aki> I've never studied this much before~ I'll
probably forget everything by tomorrow~!

\N<Hinata Aki> Wow, turns out the teacher is actually a
nice person~ I thought they would be a mean teacher!

\N<Omura> What a rude student. There's no other teacher who
cares about the students as much as this one, right?

\N<Hinata Aki> By the way, what is the simple request you
mentioned?

\N<Omura> Oh, by the way, the teacher has a friend who is a
painter.

\N<Omura> The teacher really likes the works that their
friend paints.

\N<Omura> But recently, that friend has been lamenting
about not having a good subject to paint...

\N<Omura> It's sad that even as a teacher, they can't see
his works...

\N<Omura> So... when I asked if there was anything I could
do to help, they said they wanted me to send them a photo of
a good subject, preferably a female.

\N<Omura> So I thought, how about using Aki? You're active
in sports, so you have a slim figure.

\N<Hinata Aki> Speaking of subjects for paintings... could
it be...

\N<Omura> There's no way I would tell my student to get
naked, right?
\N<Hinata Aki> So, what kind of photo is it?
\N Omura: It's easy, just lick the vegetables a little.

\N<Hinata Aki> Lick the vegetables...? Are you going to
make a painting out of that?
\N<Omura> Oh yeah, artists tend to be eccentric, you know~

\N<Omura> There are things that us ordinary people can't
understand.
\N<Hinata Aki> Hmm... so that's how it is.
\N<Hinata Aki>(I'm getting nervous for some reason)
\N<Hinata Aki> By the way, why the blindfold...?

\N<Omura> He said that by hiding a part of the face, it
stimulates the imagination.

\N<Omura> He said that he wants the subject's eyes to be
hidden as much as possible.

\N<Hinata Aki> Wow... I don't really understand, but he's
really particular about it...

\N<Omura> Then, let's have you lick the cucumber right
away.
\N<Hinata Aki>(I don't really understand what's going on)

<Hinata Aki>(If I can get money from this, I guess it's
fine)

\N<Hinata Aki>(It's not like it's a nude drawing or
anything)
\N<Hinata Aki> Is this... mmm... the right feeling?
\N<Omura> Ah, that's good... It feels nice...

\N<Omura>(I can't believe I can capture Hinata Aki in this
state...)
\N<Omura> You got this question wrong again, didn't you?

\N<Omura> It's a subject that requires memorization, so if
you remember it, you can get points, you know?

\N<Hinata Aki> I'm not good at memorizing~ It feels like
everything just goes in one ear and out the other!

\N<Omura> It's all just mistakes because you're not good at
it...

<Hinata Aki> Ahahaha... you really know how to hit where it
hurts, don't you~...

\N<Hinata Aki> But but! Thanks to Mr. Omura's teachings, my
scores on the past exams have been improving!

\N<Omura> Indeed, your scores have been gradually
improving. But really... if you put in the effort, you can
do it, so make sure to study regularly.
<Hinata Aki> Please go easy on me in my daily life...

\N<Hinata Aki> That's right...! Thanks to Mr. Omura, I was
able to buy new shoes!

\N<Omura> Oh, that's great! My artist friend was really
happy about it too.
\N<Omura> By the way... I was asked to be a subject again.

\N<Omura> If it's okay with you, Hinata Aki... what do you
think?

\N<Hinata Aki> Hmm~ It's totally fine~ It ended quickly
last time too~
\N<Omura> Hehe, then... let's get started right away...

\N<Omura> If I were to upload this image to the internet, I
could earn some money... And Aki is slowly starting to open
up to me as well...

\N<Omura> (Don't rush, little by little... I'll make you
fall...)
